  "blurb": "A hillside villa above Chaweng Noi, completed in 2024 and arranged across three levels so the sea view carries into every room. Four en-suite bedrooms, an infinity-edge pool that reads straight to the horizon, and a self-contained ground-floor studio with its own kitchenette and plunge pool. Freehold, furnished and ready to move in, about four kilometres from Chaweng's centre.",
  "detail": "Set into the hillside above Chaweng Noi on Koh Samui's east coast, this contemporary villa was completed in 2024 and laid out over three levels so that the sea view carries through the living spaces and each of the bedrooms. The result is a house that feels open and unhurried, with clean tropical lines, full-height sliding glass and a restrained palette of stone, timber and white render.\n\nThe main living level places an open-plan kitchen and lounge alongside two of the four bedrooms, opening onto a covered terrace with an outdoor lounge and sunbeds. A third bedroom occupies the top floor for the best outlook and the greatest privacy, while the ground floor holds a self-contained studio suite with its own kitchenette, sitting area and separate plunge pool — well suited to guests, staff or independent stays. All four bedrooms are en-suite, air-conditioned and furnished throughout.\n\nAt the centre of the plan is an infinity-edge pool, roughly 8.3 by 3.1 metres, that appears to spill toward the sea, framed by a generous sun terrace. The kitchen is fully fitted, the villa comes furnished, and covered parking accommodates two cars.\n\nChaweng Noi is among the island's most established residential pockets — quiet and green, yet close to the action. Chaweng's shops, restaurants and beach clubs lie about four kilometres away, with Fisherman's Village at Bophut, Lamai and the airport all an easy drive. Sold freehold on a Chanote title and ready to move in, the villa suits a family home, a private retreat or a rental holding.",
